ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Complex Verbal - Initiation/Perseveration (Naming U. S. States)
Simple Verbal - Initiation/Perseveration (Naming colors found in the room)

Notes: 0 = not able to say, 'gee-key-bee' four times;1 = able to say, 'gee-key-bee' four times
0 = not able to say, 'boh-bah-bee' four times;1 = able to say, 'boh-bah-bee' four times

ElementDescription: Double Alternating Movements 1 (Palm up/palm down,  five repetitions)
Notes: 0 = not able to perform palm up/palm down for five repetitions;1 = able to perform palm up/palm down for five repetitions
0 = not able to perform clenched/extended for five repetitions;1 = able to perform clenched/extended for five repetitions
0 = not able to perform tap left/tap right for 10 repetitions;1 = able to perform tap left/tap right for 10 repetitions

ElementDescription: Graphomotor Design 1 (Reproduction ramparts  five consecutive alternating 'square-semi circle waves')
Notes: 0 = not able to reproduce ramparts for five consecutive alternating square-semi circle waves;1 = able to reproduce ramparts for five consecutive alternating square-semi circle waves
0 = not able to reproduce semi circle;1 = able to reproduce semi circle
0 = not able to reproduce cross;1 = able to reproduce cross

ElementDescription: Graphomotor Design 4 (Reproduction of at least five consecutive alternating cross and semi circle pairs)
Notes: 0 = not able to reproduce at least five consecutive alternating cross and semi circle pairs;1 = able to reproduce at least five consecutive alternating cross and semi circle pairs
sum of all items if none are missing

-1.5 = Pre-Screening; -1 = Screening; 0 = Baseline; ## = Visit ## (from 1 to 10); Whole numbers = standard monthly visits; #.001 - #.009 = Unscheduled; #.1 = End of Phase 1; #.2 = End of Phase 2; #.3 = End of Phase 3; #.4 = End of Open Choice Phase; #.5 = End of Study; #.6 = Genetic Analysis; 1000=all visits
